The Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, governorship candidate in Bayelsa State, Senator Douye Diri, has declared that his party will emerge victorious in the November governorship election in the state. Diri said the party would emerge victorious in the forthcoming election if chieftains of the party gird their loins. In a statement by his campaign office, Diri said victory was assured if they worked in unity, adding that he will not disappoint them and the people of the state. The statement reads: “We are humbled and elated by the massive show of solidarity and the sacrifices made by the delegates to ensure that the distinguished Senator emerges victorious in what has gone down as the most competitive governorship primary in the state. “Our heartfelt gratitude also goes to our amiable leader, His Excellency the Honourable Henry Seriake Dickson, Governor of Bayelsa State for his display of uncommon political leadership and sagacity. “Let us also commend the national leadership of our party and the Governor Darius Ishaku led committee for a job well done, especially for allowing a level playing field. “We also appreciate PDP leaders and stakeholders, women, youths and Bayelsans for their support, prayers and wise counsel since we began this journey to move our state to greater heights. “We acknowledge the efforts of other aspirants who gave their best shot for the ticket. Our victory is a collective one so we enjoin them as true party men to stand with us as we move closer to make this project a reality. “In the days ahead, we shall storm communities across the eight local government areas to present to our people what we are bringing to the table in the next four years. “It is going to be an interesting voyage as we intend to use the opportunity to discuss facts on competence, prosperity of our people and stable governance as a whole.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.